ts":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"ROCHEFORT","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gaston, Adrien, Andre, Armand, Cecile, Celine, Dany, Gaetan, Herve, Jacques, Jean-Guy, Lucien.","French: habitational name from Rochefort, the name of several places in various parts of France.","English: variant of   Ratchford  . Compare   Rochford  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rocheford","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Fernand.","Altered form of French   Rochefort  ."]},{"name":"Ratchford","meanings":["habitational name from Rochford (Worcestershire), from Old English <i>ræcc</i> ‘hunting dog’ (genitive <i>ræcces</i>) + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’.","habitational name from Rochford (Essex). Early forms of the name ending in <i>Ro-</i> suggest that the placename derives from Old English <i>hrōc</i> ‘rook’ or the Old English personal name <i>Hrōc(a)</i> + Old English <i>ford</i> ‘ford’, but the 13th century forms in <i>Ra-</i> and <i>Re-</i> suggest that the first element is Old English <i>ræcc</i> ‘hunting dog’.","English:"]}]},{"name":"Alain","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Breton form of <i>Alan</i>, now common in all parts of France.  See  <b>Alan</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alain de ROCHEFORT was born on 8 January 1170, in Rochefort-en-Terre, Morbihan, Brittany, France, his father, Janorgon de Rochefort, was 36 and his mother, Théophanie de Lanvaux, was 31. He married Anne de ROSTRENEN 